  <span id="freeText1139114241607418655" style="display:none">Wonderfully written, grim and gritty, this collection of semi linear vignettes about the decline of a hardscrabble rural farming family starts harsh and keeps on goin'. Loyal Blood, the protagonist who starts the book off by murdering his woman? His life is a wildly varied parade of woes stitched I to the fabric of the 20th century. So much woe that after a while it almost verges on comedy...could see the Cohen brothers taking it that way. The ending is apropos, but if you're looking for closure, it may not satisfy.</span>
