<div id="review_3214450005" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3214450005" />
    <a title="Martina Canova" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/67718972-martina-canova"><img alt="Martina Canova" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1537547083p2/67718972.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3214450005?book_show_action=true">Mar 29, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Martina Canova" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Martina Canova" href="/user/show/67718972-martina-canova">Martina Canova</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3214450005" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14765059690945069194">A very good book to learn about American culture, especially rural life in the 20th century. I think it can be a useful starting point to talk about some themes, like the development of language and its regional variability, the role of women, psychological consequences of unbearable mistakes and the point of view of farmers, miners and similar on their contemporary society. <br/>I don&apos;t love it from the point of view of the narrative technique, but still, I suggest to read it!</span>
  <span id="freeText14765059690945069194" style="display:none">A very good book to learn about American culture, especially rural life in the 20th century. I think it can be a useful starting point to talk about some themes, like the development of language and its regional variability, the role of women, psychological consequences of unbearable mistakes and the point of view of farmers, miners and similar on their contemporary society. <br />I don't love it from the point of view of the narrative technique, but still, I suggest to read it!</span>
  <a data-text-id="14765059690945069194" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
