<div id="review_2028787602" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2028787602" />
    <a title="Janet Ashley" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/51146483-janet-ashley"><img alt="Janet Ashley" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1452108326p2/51146483.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2028787602?book_show_action=true">Jul 08, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Janet Ashley" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Janet Ashley" href="/user/show/51146483-janet-ashley">Janet Ashley</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/51146483-janet-ashley?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/51146483-janet-ashley?shelf=2017">2017</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2028787602" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11849422302433410355">Considering I was on vacation while reading this book, and it still took me the whole week to finish, it obviously wasn&apos;t a page turner for me. In fact, I nearly abandoned this book, which I don&apos;t do lightly. In the end, I&apos;m glad I finished it as I eventually began to enter this world she painted of a lost family and appreciated her way of making you feel the character&apos;s hopelessness. However, I&apos;ve never enjoyed steam of consciousness style of writing, ala Faulkner, so although I appreciated the</span>
  <span id="freeText11849422302433410355" style="display:none">Considering I was on vacation while reading this book, and it still took me the whole week to finish, it obviously wasn't a page turner for me. In fact, I nearly abandoned this book, which I don't do lightly. In the end, I'm glad I finished it as I eventually began to enter this world she painted of a lost family and appreciated her way of making you feel the character's hopelessness. However, I've never enjoyed steam of consciousness style of writing, ala Faulkner, so although I appreciated the content, I didn't love the delivery. Plus nothing was ever resolved or explained so at the end I felt a little cheated for sticking with it and having it end so adruptly.</span>
  <a data-text-id="11849422302433410355" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


